@page "/privacy"
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]

<LegalPageShell Title="Privacy policy"
                MetaDescription="How ScamAlert collects, uses, and protects personal information for your account and protected PCs."
                CanonicalPath="/privacy">

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">Overview</h2>
        <p>
            @LegalEntityName ("ScamAlert," "we," "us") provides software and online services that help families detect and respond to
            suspicious remote-access activity on Windows computers they choose to protect. This policy describes how we handle personal
            information when you use our website, account portal, and related services (the "Service").
        </p>
        <p>
            By using the Service, you agree to this policy. If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">Information we collect</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Account information:</strong> name, email address, password (stored hashed), subscription and billing identifiers processed by Stripe.</li>
            <li><strong>Trusted contacts:</strong> names and mobile phone numbers you provide for alert escalation.</li>
            <li><strong>Device information:</strong> display names, device identifiers, and technical keys used to link installed software to your account.</li>
            <li><strong>Security event data:</strong> remote-access attempt signals (for example source IP, port, protocol, timestamps) observed on protected PCs.</li>
            <li><strong>Alert and notification records:</strong> alert status, SMS delivery metadata, and acknowledgment tokens.</li>
            <li><strong>Technical logs:</strong> application logs, diagnostics, and cookies or similar technologies needed for authentication and security (see <a href="/cookies">cookie notice</a>).</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">How we use information</h2>
        <p>We use personal information to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Provide, operate, and improve the Service;</li>
            <li>Send SMS and email notifications you configure (through providers such as Twilio and email vendors);</li>
            <li>Process subscriptions and prevent fraud;</li>
            <li>Comply with law and enforce our <a href="/terms">Terms of service</a>;</li>
            <li>Respond to support requests.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not sell your personal information to data brokers for their independent marketing.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">SMS and phone numbers</h2>
        <p>
            You are responsible for ensuring you have permission to add phone numbers for security alerts and that contacts understand they may
            receive automated messages. Message frequency varies with activity. Message and data rates may apply. Contacts can reply as described
            in alert messages (for example acknowledgment instructions). Carriers are not liable for delayed or undelivered messages.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">Legal bases (where applicable)</h2>
        <p>
            For users in jurisdictions that require a legal basis, we rely on performance of our contract with you, legitimate interests in
            securing accounts and providing the Service, and consent where required (for example SMS to numbers you provide).
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">Sharing with service providers</h2>
        <p>We may share information with vendors who help us run the Service, such as:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Cloud hosting and database providers;</li>
            <li>Stripe (payments);</li>
            <li>Twilio or similar carriers (SMS);</li>
            <li>Email delivery providers;</li>
            <li>Analytics and monitoring tools.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>These providers are permitted to process data only to perform services for us under appropriate safeguards.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">Retention</h2>
        <p>
            We retain information while your account is active and for a reasonable period afterward for backups, legal compliance, and dispute
            resolution. You may request deletion subject to applicable law and technical constraints.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">Security</h2>
        <p>
            We use administrative, technical, and organizational measures designed to protect information (including encryption in transit,
            access controls, and hashed credentials). No method of transmission or storage is completely secure.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">Children</h2>
        <p>
            The Service is intended for adults. We do not knowingly collect personal information directly from children
            under 13 without appropriate parental involvement. If you believe we have done so, contact us.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">Your choices and rights</h2>
        <p>
            Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or export personal information, or to object to certain
            processing. Contact <a href="mailto:@SupportEmail">@SupportEmail</a>. We may verify your request.
        </p>
        <p>California residents may have additional rights under applicable state privacy laws; contact us to exercise them.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="h5">Changes</h2>
        <p>
            We may update this policy. We will post the new date at the top and, for material changes, provide additional notice where required.
            Continued use after changes means you accept the updated policy.
        </p>
    </section>

</LegalPageShell>

@inject IOptions<WebSiteOptions> WebOptions

@code {
    private string LegalEntityName => WebOptions.Value.LegalEntityName;
    private string SupportEmail => WebOptions.Value.SupportEmail;
}
